.TH "tb_xdomain_request" 9 "tb_xdomain_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tb_xdomain_request \- Send a XDomain request
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tb_xdomain_request
.BI "(struct tb_xdomain *xd "  ","
.BI "const void *request "  ","
.BI "size_t request_size "  ","
.BI "enum tb_cfg_pkg_type request_type "  ","
.BI "void *response "  ","
.BI "size_t response_size "  ","
.BI "enum tb_cfg_pkg_type response_type "  ","
.BI "unsigned int timeout_msec "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "xd" 12
XDomain to send the request
.IP "request" 12
Request to send
.IP "request_size" 12
Size of the request in bytes
.IP "request_type" 12
PDF type of the request
.IP "response" 12
Response is copied here
.IP "response_size" 12
Expected size of the response in bytes
.IP "response_type" 12
Expected PDF type of the response
.IP "timeout_msec" 12
Timeout in milliseconds to wait for the response
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function can be used to send XDomain control channel messages to
the other domain. The function waits until the response is received
or when timeout triggers. Whichever comes first.
.SH "RETURN"
0 in case of success and negative errno in case of failure
